obo:GO_0099186  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2921  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"A Dyn3-Homer-Shank Protein Complex Couples the EZ and the PSD\"\n- \"To further test this model, we took advantage of Homer1a, a naturally occurring activity-induced isoform of Homer that lacks its C-terminal coiled-coil domain (Sala et al., 2003). Expression of Homer1a caused a marked increase in the fraction of synapses lacking a postsynaptic EZ (percent EZ-negative synapses: control, 8.4 ± 1.8%, n = 134; Homer1a, 38.7 ± 2.6%, n = 37; Figure 4G), that was quantitatively similar to that observed upon expression of Dyn3-PRD or Dyn3-P800L (Figure 4F). Next, we tested whether the dynamin-3/Homer-dependent localization of the EZ required Homer binding to Shank. Indeed, expression of either a C-terminal fragment of Shank that binds Homer (Shank C-term) or a full-length Shank mutant lacking four amino acids required for Homer binding (ShankΔPLEF) (Sala et al., 2001; Sala et al., 2003) likewise resulted in a significant loss of PSD-associated clathrin puncta (percent EZ-negative synapses: Shank C-term, 43.7 ± 3.6%, n = 12; ShankΔPLEF, 36.8 ± 6.3%, n = 21; p < 0.001 relative to control, t-test; Figure 4G). Thus, a linear sequence of protein-protein interactions involving Shank, Homer, and dynamin-3 is required to localize EZ to the lateral margins of the PSD.\"\n\n20/01/2021 Dnyanada: Q9Z214 (HOMER1_RAT) was chosen on the basis of the biological system in which the experiment was conducted as the species of the overexpressed HOMER1b/c construct could not be retrieved.. Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from E18 rat embryos ...\"\n\n- Species of over-expressed HOMER1b/c is not stated in the publication. The authors were contacted for additional information (dd 16/3/2018, ehlers@neuro.duke.edu). Answer:" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2921" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

